==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoveling
<hw>Hov"el*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A method of securing a good
draught in chimneys by covering the top, leaving openings in the sides,
or by carrying up two of the sides higher than the other two.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>hovelling</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoven</ent>⟦br⟧
